column8:
Managed Hostingis a dedicated server that is accompanied by a full suite of technical support, maintenance and monitoring services. This differs from dedicated Web hosting, where customers are provided with their own servers but are still responsible for virtually all administrative and maintenance duties.

Foundation Hosting is a managed server and network offering that includes server hardware, hosting of the server including space and power, and use of the managed Hosting Area Network for Ethernet switching. Foundation customers will be provided a network based out-of-band (OOB) interface to access the Foundation nodes at the BIOS level, empowering Customers to install their operating system. No management or monitoring response is included with this product. SAVVIS will simply replace failed hardware.

Subject: OC 24x7 On-site Location Check

Local Access Category describes how the local loop connects to the CenturyLink National Network;

the three categories are:

CenturyLink Provided Access - CenturyLink orders the local loop from the LEC on behalf of the Customer,

Customer Provided Access - Customer orders the loop directly from the LEC and connect at a CenturyLink designated point,

Cross Connect Access - if the Customer has an executed Collocation or Direct Connect Agreement with CenturyLink, then the Customer can request a cross connect to CenturyLink National Network Services.

Local Access Category describes how the local loop connects to the CenturyLink National Network; the three categories are: CenturyLink Provided Access - CenturyLink orders the local loop from the LEC on behalf of the Customer, Customer Provided Access - Customer orders the loop directly from the LEC and connect at a CenturyLink designated point, Cross Connect Access - if the Customer has an executed Collocation or Direct Connect Agreement with CenturyLink, then the Customer can request a cross connect to CenturyLink National Network Services.

column8: Internet Port provides Customer Locations with connectivity to the Internet.  Private Ports provides WAN connectivity between Customer Locations.  Customers have the option to allocate traffic to point-to-point Layer 2 connections or Layer 3 MPLS.  Enhanced Ports provides all of the functionality of both an Internet Port and a Private Port in a consolidated communications solution.

Flat billing includes fixed rate for use of full port. Tiered billing includes adjustable bandwidth increments.  Precise Burstable is usage based billing calculated via 95th percentile method.  Data Transfer is usage-based billing calculated via true bit metering.

Card Diversity allows Customer to connect to a secondary card on the same POP as the primary card. Device Diversity allows Customer to connect to a secondary device (Gateway or Router) within the same POP as the primary device. Primary reflects the initial port for which a secondary port is diverse from.

The CenturyLink IQ Networking Transition Program addresses three components that will assist customers in migration:

1) MRC/NRC waiver for loop and port—offsets the costs associated with transitioning.

2) Professional Project Management (PPM)— assists with the resources/skill set needed to migrate while minimizing risk and managing uncertainty.

3) Termination liability waiver—removes the CenturyLink QCC contract barrier for existing Frame, ATM and Private Routed Network (PRN).

Centurylink IQ Fiber to the Customer promotion offers customers large bandwidth connectivity at increasing price discounts on ELA Access for IQ Networking with streamlined implementation for Locations in the 14-state in-region, in-franchise territory that are situated along fiber to the node (FTTN) and cell site (FTTC) routes.

 

Fiber to the Customer requires that the Local Loop Speed equal Port Bandwidth.

New Customers or Existing Customers ordering additional locations or renewing services with a Renewal Attachment, to
CenturyLink IQ Data Bundle, Data Bundle Pro, Managed Data Bundle, Managed VoIP Bundle, SIP Trunk IAD Bundle or
Integrated Access Package will be eligible to get a Discount on the In-Region (QC) Loop Component.
EFM allows for Special Construction up to 5280 feet without going to CNDC from nearest fiber splice point with RBOC fiber footprint within a ethernet disclosed serving wire center.
